abstract: The lawmaker’s comments were some of his most confrontational yet.
snippet: The lawmaker’s comments were some of his most confrontational yet.
lead_paragraph: In some of his most confrontational comments yet, Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the chairman of the House Intelligence Committee, laid out President Trump’s refusal to accept the conclusion of American intelligence agencies that Russia, not Ukraine, interfered in the 2016 presidential elections as a betrayal of the nation’s foreign policy.
headline_main: Trump’s defense of Russian election interference is an ‘intelligence coup,’ Schiff says.

abstract: The U.S. government will deport a planeload of Brazilians on Friday, the second such chartered flight since October to return an increasing number of migrants trying to enter the United States illegally from Mexico.
snippet: The U.S. government will deport a planeload of Brazilians on Friday, the second such chartered flight since October to return an increasing number of migrants trying to enter the United States illegally from Mexico.
lead_paragraph: BRASILIA — The U.S. government will deport a planeload of Brazilians on Friday, the second such chartered flight since October to return an increasing number of migrants trying to enter the United States illegally from Mexico.
headline_main: Brazil Green Lights U.S. Deportation of More Brazilians by Plane
headline_print_headline: Brazil Green Lights U.S. Deportation of More Brazilians by Plane

abstract: The Sanders campaign highlighted Mr. Rogan’s supportive comments in a video. But the podcast host has been criticized for aiding conspiracy theorists and for remarks about transgender people.
snippet: The Sanders campaign highlighted Mr. Rogan’s supportive comments in a video. But the podcast host has been criticized for aiding conspiracy theorists and for remarks about transgender people.
lead_paragraph: The entrepreneur Andrew Yang was struggling in obscurity when, about a year ago, he went on Joe Rogan’s podcast, “The Joe Rogan Experience.”

abstract: The president’s team should emphasize that President Trump had “no corrupt purpose,” the senator said, and the impeachment managers should “use the words of the other side.”
snippet: The president’s team should emphasize that President Trump had “no corrupt purpose,” the senator said, and the impeachment managers should “use the words of the other side.”
lead_paragraph: Senator Lindsey Graham, Republican of South Carolina and an impeachment manager during the Clinton trial, offered advice to both legal teams during the most recent break in the proceedings. He suggested that the president’s team should emphasize that Mr. Trump had “no corrupt purpose” and that the impeachment managers should “use the words of the other side, as they used my words — I’m fair game — talking about how they viewed executive privilege when it was a Democratic president.”

abstract: The department did not provide a House panel with records that it had requested.
snippet: The department did not provide a House panel with records that it had requested.
lead_paragraph: The State Department on Friday afternoon missed another deadline to provide documents requested by Congress, as Democratic impeachment managers accused President Trump of obstructing Congress by stonewalling documents and trying to intimidate witnesses.
headline_main: As Democrats lay out obstruction claim, the State Dept. skips another deadline.

abstract: An associate of Rudy Giuliani has provided congressional investigators with a recording of President Donald Trump saying he wanted to get rid of the U.S. ambassador to Ukraine, whose ouster emerged as an issue in the president’s impeachment, his attorney told The Associated Press on Friday.
snippet: An associate of Rudy Giuliani has provided congressional investigators with a recording of President Donald Trump saying he wanted to get rid of the U.S. ambassador to Ukraine, whose ouster emerged as an issue in the president’s impeachment, his a...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — An associate of Rudy Giuliani has provided congressional investigators with a recording of President Donald Trump saying he wanted to get rid of the U.S. ambassador to Ukraine, whose ouster emerged as an issue in the president’s impeachment, his attorney told The Associated Press on Friday.
headline_main: House Is Given Tape of Trump Calling for Ambassador's Ouster
headline_print_headline: House Is Given Tape of Trump Calling for Ambassador's Ouster

abstract: The argument appeared to be aimed not only at the public, but also at Republican senators who have signaled a willingness to support a measure that would introduce new witnesses and documents.
snippet: The argument appeared to be aimed not only at the public, but also at Republican senators who have signaled a willingness to support a measure that would introduce new witnesses and documents.
lead_paragraph: Hours after a recording emerged of President Trump apparently ordering the removal of the American envoy to Ukraine, Democratic impeachment managers, laying out their case that Mr. Trump obstructed Congress, sought to weaponize all the evidence still being withheld from lawmakers.
headline_main: Citing White House obstruction, managers weaponize the unknown.
